Preheat the oven to 150C/130C Fan/Gas 2.Roughly chop the new potatoes into quarters, but at odd angles.Heat a dash of olive oil in an oven dish. Add the potatoes and brown them on the hob over a moderate heat.Roughly chop the hazelnuts.Heat the butter in a pan until it is almost going a nutty brown colour.Pour the butter over the potatoes and mix in the hazelnuts.Bake in the oven for one hour 30 minutes, or until the potatoes are crisp and golden-brown.